SIMPLE: turmoil
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turmoil
<hw>Tur"moil</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r"moil)</pr> <it>sometimes</it>
<pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r*moil")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of uncertain origin;
perhaps fr. OF. <ets>tremouille</ets> the hopper of a mill,
<ets>trembler</ets> to tremble (cf. E. <ets>tremble</ets>); influenced
by E. <ets>turn</ets> and <ets>moil</ets>.]</ety> <def>Harassing labor;
trouble; molestation by tumult; disturbance; worrying
confusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And there I'll rest, as after much <qex>turmoil</qex>,⟦br⟧
A blessed soul doth in Elysium.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1553 pr=PI -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turmoil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Turmoil
<hw>Tur*moil"</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r*moil")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Turmoiled</conjf>
<pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r*moil"d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Turmoiling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To harass with commotion; to
disquiet; to worry.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is her fatal misfortune . . . to be miserably tossed and
<qex>turmoiled</qex> with these storms of affliction.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turmoil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Turmoil
<hw>Tur*moil"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be disquieted or confused;
to be in commotion.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turn</ent>⟦br⟧
